<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
[f]:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Forward
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2206001003">
<title>
Toe Adjustment
</title>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Never adjust only right side or left side tie-rod. Be sure to adjust both tie-rods by the same amount.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Make sure that rack boot is not twisted. Otherwise, rack boot may be broken.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Loosen tie-rod end lock nuts.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Tighten or loosen right and left tie-rods by the same amount to adjust toe to specification.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that length “a” on right tie-rod is equal to that on left tie-rod. If they are not equal, readjust toe.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A220002.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "32.664mm" ver = "02" gw = "240" gh = "76"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
After adjustment, tighten tie-rod end lock nuts to specified torque. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A6306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2206001004">
<title>
Reference Information
</title>
<topic id = "AENAP70A2206001005">
<title>
Side slip
</title>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Side slip (On one person)
</sdm-title>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0 to IN 3 mm/m (0 to IN 0.12 in./3.3 ft.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
</topic>
<topic id = "AENAP70A2206001006">
<title>
Toe angle
</title>
<ptxt>
Reference front toe angle when measured using total wheel alignment tester or the like, is as follow.
</ptxt>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Front toe angle (Each wheel)
</sdm-title>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
IN 0&#176; 03’ ± 0&#176; 05’
</sdm-value>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
<ptxt>
If front toe angle is out of specification, measure total toe using toe-in gauge and then adjust it at the tie-rod.
</ptxt>
</topic>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70A2206001007">
<title>
Camber, Caster and Kingpin Inclination Angle Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
Check camber, caster and kingpin inclination angle using camber caster kingpin gauge (1) and turning radius gauge (2). If measured value is out of specified value, check following items for damage, deformation and cracks. Repair or replace any defective part.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Strut assembly components
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Suspension arms and bushings
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Front suspension frame
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Front wheel hubs, steering knuckles and wheel bearings
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Vehicle body
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Camber, caster and kingpin inclination angle are not adjustable. If they are out of specification, repair vehicle body or replace related part.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7RS0A220003.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.143mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "123"/>
</figure>
